# The e2e build suite runs these fixtures from a build-tree COPY (see
# ../e2e/CMakeLists.txt), so a normal `ctest` run never writes here and the
# checkout stays clean — no per-fixture binary names to enumerate.
#
# These rules are a defensive guard for a stray *manual* `topo-build` inside a
# fixture: ignore the output KINDS, never individual files. Scoped to this
# fixtures subtree, so the tracked test/topo-passes-sidecar/ *.topo-passes/
# JSON fixtures are unaffected.
**/build/
**/.topo-cache/
**/target/
*.dSYM/
*.ll
*.topo-passes/
Cargo.lock
